Isn't your... (GRUNTING)

260
00:11:05.580 --> 00:11:07.040
...plan working?

261
00:11:07.040 --> 00:11:08.500
I'm... Ow!

262
00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:09.620
...fine.

263
00:11:09.620 --> 00:11:11.210
I know exactly... (YELPS)

264
00:11:11.210 --> 00:11:12.499
...what I'm doing.

265
00:11:12.499 --> 00:11:14.289
I hope they make it.

266
00:11:14.290 --> 00:11:16.500
This is definitely... (GRUNTS)

267
00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:17.880
...the right way, Kiara.

268
00:11:17.880 --> 00:11:20.620
I'm almost through!

269
00:11:20.620 --> 00:11:22.750
And I'm almost at the branch.

270
00:11:22.750 --> 00:11:24.579
After that it'll be...
(GROANS)

271
00:11:24.579 --> 00:11:26.419
...easy!
Right, Mom?

272
00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:27.500
Mom?

273
00:11:27.830 --> 00:11:28.920
Mom?

274
00:11:28.920 --> 00:11:31.210
(BOTH GROANING AND GRUNTING)

275
00:11:39.290 --> 00:11:40.750
BOTH: Mom?

276
00:11:42.330 --> 00:11:45.710
Now they're truly on
the Trail to Udugu.

277
00:11:45.710 --> 00:11:48.380
SIMBA: That was so exciting.

278
00:11:48.380 --> 00:11:50.169
Your first rescue
with the King.

279
00:11:51.750 --> 00:11:54.540
I wonder what our next
challenge will be.

280
00:11:55.920 --> 00:11:58.830
Well, let's go, Lion Guard.

281
00:11:58.870 --> 00:12:01.750
At least he's not mad at us
for almost losing that egg.

282
00:12:01.750 --> 00:12:02.789
Why should he be?

283
00:12:02.790 --> 00:12:05.790
It's not your fault
you can't jump like a lion.

284
00:12:05.831 --> 00:12:09.751
What's the point of being
a team if we're all
gonna do the same thing?

285
00:12:09.751 --> 00:12:12.080
Fuli, he's the King!

286
00:12:12.080 --> 00:12:14.539
He's gotta know
what he's doing.

287
00:12:14.540 --> 00:12:15.830
Doesn't he?

288
00:12:15.830 --> 00:12:19.330
Maybe we just need to do it
more Simba's way?

289
00:12:19.330 --> 00:12:21.710
Everyone!
Everyone!

290
00:12:21.710 --> 00:12:23.670
The gazelles...
The gazelles
need our help!

291
00:12:23.670 --> 00:12:25.539
Lion Guard, follow me!

292
00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:29.750
(SIGHS) That's what I was
going to say...

293
00:12:30.830 --> 00:12:32.330
KIARA: Mom?

294
00:12:32.330 --> 00:12:33.420
Mom!

295
00:12:34.709 --> 00:12:36.919
No sign of Mom on my side.

296
00:12:36.919 --> 00:12:38.119
Have you found anything?

297
00:12:39.290 --> 00:12:40.290
Kion?

298
00:12:42.580 --> 00:12:43.830
Nothing over here.

299
00:12:43.830 --> 00:12:45.580
(SIGHS SOFTLY)
How could she just disappear?

300
00:12:47.619 --> 00:12:48.619
Mom!

301
00:12:49.579 --> 00:12:50.829
We'll find her.

302
00:12:50.830 --> 00:12:52.710
We just have
to keep looking.

303
00:12:52.710 --> 00:12:53.830
Try your side again.

304
00:12:53.830 --> 00:12:55.790
I tried my side.

305
00:12:55.790 --> 00:12:57.830
If she was there
I'd have seen her.

306
00:12:57.830 --> 00:13:00.500
I know, I just...

307
00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:02.169
I can't find her either.

308
00:13:02.170 --> 00:13:05.210
If we knew where
this Udugu place was,

309
00:13:05.210 --> 00:13:07.420
maybe we could
meet her there.

310
00:13:07.420 --> 00:13:09.040
Or we could track her.

311
00:13:09.790 --> 00:13:11.960
(SNIFFING)

312
00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:13.709
Got her!

313
00:13:13.709 --> 00:13:14.829
She went this way.

314
00:13:14.830 --> 00:13:15.670
Come on!

315
00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:19.880
(KIARA SNIFFS)

316
00:13:20.580 --> 00:13:21.670
Kiara, look!

317
00:13:21.670 --> 00:13:23.500
Paw prints.

318
00:13:23.500 --> 00:13:24.709
They look fresh.

319
00:13:25.919 --> 00:13:27.709
We must be getting close.

320
00:13:27.710 --> 00:13:28.790
Come on.

321
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:32.710
(SNIFFING)

322
00:13:32.710 --> 00:13:33.920
What?

323
00:13:33.920 --> 00:13:35.710
They just stop
right here?

324
00:13:35.710 --> 00:13:37.249
<i>Heyvi kabisa!</i>

325
00:13:37.249 --> 00:13:38.789
Where did Mom go?

326
00:13:41.830 --> 00:13:43.920
The gazelles are just
over the next ridge.

327
00:13:45.880 --> 00:13:46.960
There!

328
00:13:50.120 --> 00:13:54.120
Swala and the other gazelles
must be looking for a route
up to that grassland.

329
00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:56.290
But those rocks...
They're unstable.

330
00:13:56.290 --> 00:13:58.920
The rocks will fall if
the gazelles jump on them.

331
00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:01.959
Lion Guard, follow me!

332
00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:05.660
Should we remind him
how easily gazelles spook
when they're surprised?

333
00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:07.960
Nah! Simba knows
what he's doing.

334
00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:09.620
It'll be fine.

335
00:14:14.420 --> 00:14:15.460
What's that?

336
00:14:17.250 --> 00:14:18.380
Something's coming!

337
00:14:18.380 --> 00:14:19.620
ALL: (PANICKED)
Something's coming!

338
00:14:19.620 --> 00:14:21.290
Something's coming!
Something's coming!

339
00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:23.710
They're spooked.

340
00:14:23.710 --> 00:14:25.579
Now we really need to hurry.

341
00:14:25.579 --> 00:14:26.959
Lion Guard, follow me!

342
00:14:30.920 --> 00:14:32.580
(GROUND RUMBLING)

343
00:14:35.419 --> 00:14:36.789
Everyone, stop!

344
00:14:36.789 --> 00:14:38.119
The cliff is collapsing!

345
00:14:39.790 --> 00:14:41.580
Ono, warn Simba!

346
00:14:41.580 --> 00:14:42.620
Affirmative!

347
00:14:54.540 --> 00:14:56.080
(GASPS) Oh, no!

348
00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:57.170
Simba!

349
00:14:58.539 --> 00:14:59.709
Your Majesty?

350
00:15:00.209 --> 00:15:01.419
Simba!

351
00:15:01.919 --> 00:15:05.039
(SIMBA COUGHING)

352
00:15:05.040 --> 00:15:06.830
Good to see you, Ono.

353
00:15:06.830 --> 00:15:08.250
Your Majesty!

354
00:15:08.250 --> 00:15:11.040
Everyone, he's over here.

355
00:15:11.040 --> 00:15:12.249
Are you all right?

356
00:15:12.249 --> 00:15:13.419
I'm okay.

357
00:15:13.419 --> 00:15:14.959
Just a little stuck.

358
00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:19.750
This can't be right.

359
00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:22.120
Mom couldn't just disappear.

360
00:15:22.120 --> 00:15:23.880
I don't get it.

361
00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:25.209
We followed her trail.

362
00:15:25.209 --> 00:15:27.209
How can it just end?

363
00:15:27.210 --> 00:15:28.880
Maybe it doesn't.

364
00:15:28.880 --> 00:15:30.790
There's a ledge
and a trail.

365
00:15:32.540 --> 00:15:34.120
I bet Mom jumped up there.

366
00:15:34.999 --> 00:15:36.619
Then we will too.

367
00:15:36.619 --> 00:15:37.829
Ready?

368
00:15:37.829 --> 00:15:39.959
One, two, three!

369
00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:42.750
(BOTH GRUNTING)

370
00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:45.080
Not even close.

371
00:15:45.080 --> 00:15:47.540
If Mom could get up there,
we can too.

372
00:15:47.540 --> 00:15:50.329
Mom's twice
our size, Kion.

373
00:15:50.329 --> 00:15:52.829
How can we keep tracking her
if we can't jump up?

374
00:15:53.580 --> 00:15:54.920
I've got it!

375
00:15:54.961 --> 00:15:58.161
I'll give you a boost,
then you can
keep tracking her.

376
00:15:58.161 --> 00:15:59.750
But what about you?

377
00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:02.079
One of us has
to boost the other,

378
00:16:02.079 --> 00:16:04.499
and the truth is...

379
00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:05.920
You're the better tracker.

380
00:16:05.920 --> 00:16:07.830
I won't argue that.

381
00:16:07.871 --> 00:16:11.711
Though you're the one
who saw the tracks
and figured out Mom jumped.

382
00:16:11.711 --> 00:16:13.619
So we make a good team.

383
00:16:13.619 --> 00:16:15.209
And that's how
we'll find Mom,

384
00:16:15.210 --> 00:16:16.880
by working together.

385
00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:19.120
Now up you go.

386
00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:20.790
(STRAINING)

387
00:16:22.250 --> 00:16:24.460
Whoa!
I gotcha! Hang on.

388
00:16:25.079 --> 00:16:26.879
(STRAINING)

389
00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:28.710
Just a little closer.

390
00:16:31.120 --> 00:16:32.250
How's that?

391
00:16:32.250 --> 00:16:35.000
(STRAINING) I think
I'm gonna make it.

392
00:16:35.669 --> 00:16:36.749
Yes! (PANTING)

393
00:16:37.579 --> 00:16:38.709
We did it!

394
00:16:40.580 --> 00:16:43.120
(GASPS) I don't believe it.

395
00:16:43.120 --> 00:16:45.380
Kiara, what's going on?

396
00:16:46.040 --> 00:16:47.500
Hello down there.

397
00:16:48.919 --> 00:16:50.329
(CHUCKLES) Mom!

398
00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:57.540
Mom, why did
you disappear?

399
00:16:57.540 --> 00:17:00.290
I thought you were gonna
show us the way to Udugu.

400
00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:02.879
Actually, I think you've
already found Udugu.

401
00:17:03.670 --> 00:17:05.170
We have?

402
00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:06.710
Is it that big rock?

403
00:17:06.710 --> 00:17:07.830
No, Kion.

404
00:17:07.830 --> 00:17:09.920
Come on down, Kiara,
and I'll explain.

405
00:17:09.920 --> 00:17:11.960
Uh, okay.

406
00:17:13.289 --> 00:17:16.079
You see, kids,
Udugu isn't a place.

407
00:17:16.080 --> 00:17:19.120
Udugu is another word
for kinship.

408
00:17:19.120 --> 00:17:22.120
It's the special bond
between siblings.

409
00:17:22.161 --> 00:17:26.461
You found Udugu when
you decided to work
together to look for me.

410
00:17:26.461 --> 00:17:28.039
We did?
Yes.

411
00:17:28.040 --> 00:17:30.080
And I'm very proud of you.

412
00:17:32.210 --> 00:17:34.830
Un-Bunga-lievable.

413
00:17:34.830 --> 00:17:36.579
You're one lucky lion.

414
00:17:36.579 --> 00:17:38.419
You could have
gotten smushed.

415
00:17:38.419 --> 00:17:40.079
Don't worry,
Your Majesty.

416
00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:41.210
We'll get you free.

417
00:17:41.210 --> 00:17:42.670
(OSTRICHES SCREAMING)

418
00:17:43.830 --> 00:17:45.170
That sounds like...
Ostriches!

419
00:17:52.830 --> 00:17:54.620
(GASPS) <i>Hapana!</i>

420
00:17:54.620 --> 00:17:56.460
It's... Oh, uh...

421
00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:58.080
Well?
It's what?

422
00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:00.040
Sorry. I thought
you were going to say it.

423
00:18:00.040 --> 00:18:01.669
The gazelles!

424
00:18:01.710 --> 00:18:04.040
They're stampeding straight
for the ostriches
and their nest!

425
00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:05.710
Bad day to be
an ostrich egg.

426
00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:08.000
Your Majesty,
what do we do?

427
00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:09.330
You have to stop
the gazelles.

428
00:18:09.330 --> 00:18:10.750
And leave you here?

429
00:18:10.750 --> 00:18:12.670
I'll be fine.
You need to hurry.

430
00:18:12.670 --> 00:18:14.379
(ROCKS TUMBLING)

431
00:18:14.379 --> 00:18:16.289
Everyone, heads up!
(GASPS)

432
00:18:16.920 --> 00:18:17.920
(CRASHES)

433
00:18:19.080 --> 00:18:20.710
(COUGHING)

434
00:18:20.710 --> 00:18:22.580
Whew!
Thanks, Fuli.

435
00:18:22.580 --> 00:18:24.380
Thank Ono.
He saw the boulder.

436
00:18:24.380 --> 00:18:26.249
We all try to do
what we do best.

437
00:18:26.249 --> 00:18:28.079
That's why we're
a great team.

438
00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:30.290
That is why, isn't it?

439
00:18:30.290 --> 00:18:32.380
We can't leave Simba here.
It's not safe.

440
00:18:32.380 --> 00:18:34.580
But he told us to go
after the gazelles.

441
00:18:34.580 --> 00:18:36.120
Lion Guard!

442
00:18:36.160 --> 00:18:39.120
All day I've been telling
you to follow me,
and do what I do.

443
00:18:39.120 --> 00:18:42.000
But that's not how
your team works.

444
00:18:43.120 --> 00:18:44.380
So tell me.

445
00:18:44.380 --> 00:18:47.920
If I were Kion,
how would you handle this?

446
00:18:47.920 --> 00:18:49.119
FULI: We'd split up.

447
00:18:49.119 --> 00:18:50.669
Ono and I would go
after the herd.

448
00:18:50.669 --> 00:18:52.999
Beshte and Bunga
would stay to free you.

449
00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:55.460
Then those are my orders.

450
00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:56.880
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

451
00:18:56.880 --> 00:18:59.120
There's one more thing
Kion would do.

452
00:18:59.120 --> 00:19:00.289
Right?

453
00:19:01.959 --> 00:19:03.999
Till the Pride Lands end...

454
00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:06.170
ALL: Lion Guard defend!

455
00:19:06.170 --> 00:19:08.000
(PANICKED SCREAMING)

456
00:19:14.579 --> 00:19:16.249
I'll calm the ostriches.

457
00:19:16.250 --> 00:19:17.580
You talk to the gazelles.

458
00:19:17.580 --> 00:19:18.710
Affirmative!

459
00:19:18.710 --> 00:19:21.250
Just remember,
be soft and soothing.

460
00:19:21.250 --> 00:19:22.620
You know me!

461
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:29.670
Hey, ostriches!

462
00:19:30.250 --> 00:19:31.920
Ostriches!

463
00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:33.080
Ostriches!

464
00:19:33.080 --> 00:19:34.500
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

465
00:19:34.500 --> 00:19:36.080
(SHOUTS) Quiet!

466
00:19:36.080 --> 00:19:38.249
(SCREAMING STOPS)

467
00:19:38.249 --> 00:19:40.209
(SIGHS) That's better.

468
00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:42.880
Hello? Swala, gazelles,

469
00:19:42.880 --> 00:19:44.170
please slow down.

470
00:19:44.170 --> 00:19:46.540
What's that, Ono?
Can't hear you.

471
00:19:46.540 --> 00:19:48.330
(CLEARS THROAT)
I said...

472
00:19:48.330 --> 00:19:51.079
Whoa! Everybody,
I can't hear Ono.

473
00:19:51.079 --> 00:19:53.039
Quiet! Stop!

474
00:19:57.120 --> 00:19:59.290
Now, what were
you saying, Ono?

475
00:19:59.290 --> 00:20:01.579
Uh, never mind.

476
00:20:03.119 --> 00:20:05.289
ONO: That was weird.

477
00:20:05.290 --> 00:20:06.580
How'd you calm the ostriches?

478
00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:10.040
Soft and soothing.

479
00:20:10.040 --> 00:20:11.420
Just like you said.

480
00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:12.959
Don't worry,
Your Highness.

481
00:20:12.959 --> 00:20:15.169
We'll have you
out of there in no time.

482
00:20:15.169 --> 00:20:16.879
(SOFTLY) Careful, Big B.

483
00:20:16.921 --> 00:20:19.211
If you let the boulder
roll the wrong way
it'll squish him.

484
00:20:19.211 --> 00:20:22.670
Bunga, you know
I can hear you, right?

485
00:20:22.670 --> 00:20:25.960
Uh, sure, I knew that.

486
00:20:25.960 --> 00:20:28.329
Did you know that?
Yep.

487
00:20:28.330 --> 00:20:30.500
BESHTE: <i>Twende Kiboko!</i>

488
00:20:30.500 --> 00:20:32.080
(BESHTE GRUNTS)
All clear!

489
00:20:33.670 --> 00:20:35.420
(RUMBLING)

490
00:20:37.329 --> 00:20:38.749
BUNGA: Uh-oh.

491
00:20:38.749 --> 00:20:40.379
Let's get out of here!

492
00:20:45.670 --> 00:20:48.120
(ALL PANTING)
Whoo!

493
00:20:48.120 --> 00:20:51.249
That was un-Bunga-lievable!

494
00:20:51.249 --> 00:20:52.289
I kinda wanna do it again.

495
00:20:52.290 --> 00:20:54.170
Nice job, guys.

496
00:20:54.170 --> 00:20:57.290
Simba's safe, and so are
the gazelles and ostriches.

497
00:20:57.290 --> 00:20:59.830
That's because
you did it your way.

498
00:20:59.830 --> 00:21:01.499
Kion would be proud of you.

499
00:21:01.499 --> 00:21:03.329
And so am I.

500
00:21:06.540 --> 00:21:09.290
So, everyone,
how was your journey?

501
00:21:09.290 --> 00:21:11.540
Did you find Udugu?

502
00:21:11.540 --> 00:21:12.749
We found it.

503
00:21:12.749 --> 00:21:14.209
But it's not really
a place.

504
00:21:14.209 --> 00:21:17.249
It's about us working together
as brother and sister.

505
00:21:17.790 --> 00:21:18.790
As a team.

506
00:21:20.580 --> 00:21:22.290
How did things go
with the Guard?

507
00:21:22.290 --> 00:21:24.290
Well, in a way,

508
00:21:24.290 --> 00:21:27.329
the Guard helped me
find Udugu, too.

509
00:21:27.329 --> 00:21:28.879
It's an important lesson.

510
00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:32.250
It is,
especially for you two.

511
00:21:36.289 --> 00:21:38.209
And as Queen
of the Pride Lands

512
00:21:38.209 --> 00:21:40.209
and leader
of the Lion Guard,

513
00:21:40.210 --> 00:21:43.880
someday you will be
responsible for all of this.

514
00:21:50.289 --> 00:21:52.499
So hold on to what
you learned today.

515
00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:55.670
Then you'll always
have Udugu.

